    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nLet's take this one step at a time! Click the arrow to expand the step when you're ready.\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">1. Add a <code>Painter</code> parameter to the function</span>]\r\nLook at the `take_three_paint()` function near the top of the code.\r\n\r\nThe function is missing a **parameter**. Add `this_painter` inside the parentheses so it knows which `Painter` to use.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">2. Update the function to use the parameter</span>]\r\nInside the function, update the code so it uses `this_painter` instead of `sofia`. This will allow the same function to work with any `Painter`.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">3. Update the function call</span>]\r\nScroll down and look at the how the function is called. Right now, it's just `take_three_paint()`, but that's missing something!\r\n\r\nUpdate the function call to pass in `sofia` as the argument.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">4. Call the function with <code>caleb</code> as the argument</span>]\r\nKeep scrolling and look for the other `TODO`.\r\n\r\nReplace the three lines where `caleb` takes paint with a single call to your function, this time passing in `caleb`\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/eb0121e000a412190cb6ce05b38196f0-choiceA.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo make your function flexible, use a parameter like `this_painter` so the function works with any `Painter` you choose.\r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef paint_line(this_painter):\r\n  this_painter.take_paint()\r\n  this_painter.paint(\"white\")\r\n  this_painter.move()\r\n\r\npaint_line(south_side_painter)\r\n```",
